The paper deals with predicting user preferences for documents, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of latent group structures for both users and documents is a technique commonly used in collaborative filtering (cs.CL) and recommendation systems (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Gibbs sampling, which is a popular method in Bayesian inference (cs.SI).
